sentences: Randy graduated from Gilroy High School in Gilroy, California in 1982.
In 1990, Randy started at A&M Records as VP of Promotions where he worked with Janet Jackson, Sheryl Crow, Soundgarden, and Bryan Adams.
In 1998, he became President of Motion Picture Music at Miramax Films where he worked on Chicago, Shakespeare in Love, Cold Mountain and Finding Neverland.
Randy joined Paramount in 2006 as Executive Vice President of Music and Creative Affairs.
In 2007, he was promoted to President of Motion Picture Music.
In 2011, Randy was honored by the T.J. Martell Foundation and was the recipient of the T.J. Martell Foundation's "Humanitarian Award".
Additionally, in 2007, Randy received the "Joseph Papp Racial Harmony Award" from the Foundation for Ethic Understanding.
In 2012, Spendlove was ranking Number 69 on Billboard's Power 100 list.
Randy Spendlove won a 2004 Grammy for Best Soundtrack Album for a Motion Picture for Chicago.
As President of Motion Picture Music at Paramount Pictures, Randy Spendlove oversees all aspects of film music, where he has worked with such artists as Beyonc√©, Linkin Park, Green Day, and U2.
